"Soden B.J., Jackson D.L., Ramaswamy V., Schwarzkopf M.D., Huang X.","The radiative signature of upper tropospheric moistening",2005,"Science","310","5749",,"841","844",,,10.1126/science.1115602,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-27644469907&partnerID=40&md5=b7a2df47b26148f93612a4a1371337b5","Rosenstiel School for Marine and Atmospheric Science, University of Miami, Miami, FL 33149, United States; Cooperative Institute for Research in Environmental Sciences, University of Colorado, Boulder, CO 80305, United States; Geophysical Fluid Dynamics Laboratory, National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration, Princeton, NJ 08542, United States; Atmospheric and Oceanic Sciences Program, Princeton University, Princeton, NJ 08542, United States","Soden, B.J., Rosenstiel School for Marine and Atmospheric Science, University of Miami, Miami, FL 33149, United States; Jackson, D.L., Cooperative Institute for Research in Environmental Sciences, University of Colorado, Boulder, CO 80305, United States; Ramaswamy, V., Geophysical Fluid Dynamics Laboratory, National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration, Princeton, NJ 08542, United States; Schwarzkopf, M.D., Geophysical Fluid Dynamics Laboratory, National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration, Princeton, NJ 08542, United States; Huang, X., Atmospheric and Oceanic Sciences Program, Princeton University, Princeton, NJ 08542, United States","Climate models predict that the concentration of water vapor in the upper troposphere could double by the end of the century as a result of increases in greenhouse gases. Such moistening plays a key role in 'amplifying the rate at which the climate warms in response to anthropogenic activities, but has been difficult to detect because of deficiencies in conventional observing systems. We use satellite measurements to highlight a distinct radiative signature of upper tropospheric moistening over the period 1982 to 2004. The observed moistening is accurately captured by climate model simulations and lends further credence to model projections of future global warming.",,"Climatology; Clouds; Greenhouse effect; Mathematical models; Moisture; Troposphere; Vapors; Climate models; Climate warms; Tropospheric moistening; Water vapor; Radiation effects; climate modeling; troposphere; water vapor; article; climate; concentration (parameters); greenhouse effect; greenhouse gas; model; moisture; priority journal; radiation; telecommunication; troposphere; water vapor",,,,,,"Kiehl, J., Trenberth, K., (1997) Bull. Am. Meteorol. Soc., 78, p. 197; Cubasch, U., Cess, R., Climate Change: The IPCC Identific Assessment, 1990. , J. T. Houghton et Al., Eds. (Cambridge Univ. Press, Cambridge); Cess, R., (1990) J. Geophys. Res., 95, p. 16601; Raval, A., Ramathan, V., (1989) Nature, 342, p. 758; Pierrehumbert, R., (1995) J. Atmos. Sci., 52, p. 1784; Rind, D., (1991) Nature, 349, p. 500; Del Genio, A., Kovari, W., Mao-Sung, Y., (1994) Geophys. Res. Lett., 21, p. 2701; Stocker, T., (2001) Climate Change 2001: Contribution of Working Group I to the Third Assessment Report of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change, pp. 418-470. , Cambridge Univ. Press, Cambridge; Held, I., Soden, B., (2000) Annu. Rev. Energy Environ., 25, p. 441; Colman, R., (2004) Geophys. Res. Lett., 31, pp. L21109; Wetherald, R., Manabe, S., (1988) J. Atmos. Sci., 45, p. 1397; Soden, B.J., Wetherald, R.T., Stenchikov, G.L., (2002) A. Robock, Science, 296, p. 727; Lindzen, R., (1990) Bull. Am. Meteorol. Soc., 71, p. 288; Dickinson, R.E., (1996) Climate Change 7995: The Science of Climate Change, pp. 193-227. , J. T. Houghton et Al., Eds. (Cambridge Univ. Press, Cambridge); Sun, D., Lindzen, R., (1993) J. Atmos. Sci., 50, p. 1643; Lindzen, R., (2001) Bull. Am. Meteorol. Soc., 82, p. 417; Minschwaner, K., Dessler, A., (2004) J. Clim., 17, p. 1272; notenotenoteSee supporting data on Science OnlineRoss, R., Elliott, W., (2001) J. Clim., 14, p. 1602; Zhai, P., Eskridge, R., (1997) J. Clim., 10, p. 2